        public ResponseContainer processRequest(java.lang.String pathInfo,
                               java.lang.String queryString,
                               java.lang.String method,
                               de.general.log.ILogInterface log)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
        This method is called by JETTY to get a request processed. This method does not implement the request processing logic itself: This is done in the private method __processRequest0(). This method does primarily perform some debug logic.
        Parameters:
        pathInfo - The requested HTTP path
        queryString - The requested HTTP query
        method - The method requested - "GET" or "POST"
        log - A logger
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
